.agents/tasks/prd.json:384:      "description": "Phase context:\n\n# Quality, Security, And Release Context\n\nThese tasks verify the rewrite is shippable. They should be completed after feature work and kept updated as features evolve.\n\nRequired evidence:\n\n- Unit tests for domain algorithms.\n- Component tests for critical UI flows.\n- Server tests for owner authorization and mutation rules.\n- Manual smoke test checklist for auth, upload, create/edit, feed, public sharing, sessions, and migration.\n- Production readiness for environment variables, storage access, and observability.\n\nGoal:\n\nVerify that private data and storage access are owner-scoped and public sharing exposes only intended data.\n\nImplementation:\n\n1. Review every Convex query and mutation.\n2. Confirm private APIs call the auth helper.\n3. Confirm private APIs filter or fetch by authenticated owner.\n4. Confirm mutations reject records owned by another user.\n5. Confirm public step API returns only fields needed by the public page.\n6. Confirm sessions are not public unless explicitly intended.\n7. Review upload/storage paths:\n   - Owner-scoped Google Cloud Storage object keys.\n   - No cross-user overwrites.\n   - Signed upload URLs require authenticated ownership.\n   - Public playback uses short-lived signed Google Cloud Storage read URLs intentionally.\n8. Document the access model in a security note.\n\nTracer/phase plan:\n\n1. Tracer: document current auth model and one owner-isolation proof.\n2. Review Convex private/public API field exposure.\n3. Review GCS object keys, signed upload/read URL boundaries.\n4. Add missing tests/fixes discovered by review.\n5. Finalize security note.\n\nLikely files:\n\n- Create `docs/security-access-model.md`.\n- Update tests from task 1 if any missing access case is found.\n- Update Convex APIs if any authorization gap is found.\n- `docs/security-access-model.md`\n- `convex/*`\n- `lib/video/*`\n- `tests/convex/*`\n- `tests/security/*`\n\nVerification:\n\nRun:\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- --run\nnpm run typecheck\nnpm run lint\n```\n\nManual checks:\n\n- User A cannot open User B private step edit URL.\n- User A cannot mutate User B step/session through direct function calls.\n- Signed-out user can open public step page only.\n- Signed-out user cannot list private steps or sessions.\n\nUnresolved questions:\n\n- Which monitoring/logging system should be referenced for auth/storage failures?\n\nSource files:\n\n- Task: .agents/tasks/8 - quality security and release/2 - perform security and access review.md\n- Plan: .agents/tasks/8 - quality security and release/2 - perform security and access review.plan.md\n- Context: .agents/tasks/8 - quality security and release/context.md",
